Argentine Stocks: BBVA, Banco Hipotecario, Petroleo Brasileiro

-- B y   C a m i l a   R u s s o
-- 
2011-07-25T21:24:26Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-25/argentine-stocks-ypf-siderar-petroleo-brasileiro-advance.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Argentine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 4 p.m. New York time.  The Merval Index fell 0.8 percent to 3,330.88.  Banks declined in line with lenders worldwide after
President Barack Obama and Congress failed to reach a deal to
raise the debt limit, increasing concern that the U.S. will
default.  BBVA Banco Frances SA (FRAN AF) lost 2.5 percent to 13.50
pesos.  Banco Hipotecario SA (BHIP)   dropped 2.5 percent to
2.35 pesos.  Petroleo Brasileiro SA (PETR4)   rose 2.4 percent to 71.70
pesos. The oil and gas producer said it will boost debt and sell
assets after approving a $224.7 billion investment plan.  Siderar SAIC (ERAR)  ,  Argentina ’s largest steel producer,
rose 0.3 percent to 34.20 pesos. Argentina’s government named
three board members to Ternium SA’s local unit, ending a three-
month dispute with controlling shareholders of  Latin America ’s
second-largest steelmaker.  Sociedad Comercial del Plata SA (COME)  , a holding
company that produces and transports petroleum products and
natural gas through its subsidiaries, fell 2.6 percent to 0.755
pesos as oil declined for the first time in five days.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Camila Russo in  Buenos Aires  at 
